Prerequisites

• VMware Workstation installed on host system
• ESXi ISO image available
• Basic knowledge of virtual machine creation

Steps

Open VMware Workstation and click on Create New Virtual Machine.

Select Typical configuration and proceed.

Choose Installer Disc Image (ISO) and browse to select the ESXi ISO file.

Provide a name for the virtual machine and choose the storage location.

Allocate required hardware resources such as processors and RAM (for example 16 GB RAM).

Select Network Address Translation (NAT) for networking.

Choose SCSI as the disk controller and select Split virtual disk into multiple files.

Complete the wizard and power on the virtual machine.

Follow the ESXi installation prompts, accept the license, select disk, set root password, and install ESXi.

Reboot the virtual machine after installation completes.

Enable SSH by pressing F2, navigating to Troubleshooting Options, and enabling SSH.

Access the ESXi Host Client by entering the ESXi IP address in a web browser.

Upload an operating system ISO to the datastore and create a new virtual machine.

Install VMware Tools inside the guest OS.

Verify deployment by copying files to the VM desktop.
